text:
This was the first rhythm game I got addicted to. The songs are soooo good! The waifus so precious! Played it quasi religiously everyday for a year and half, both EN and JP versions, until my phone threatened to brick on it. Now I'm crippled by lag and reduced battery life. Phone is too used up to handle video games. Needs a replacement eventually. I considered (okay to be honest still considering) buying one of those overpriced gaming dedicated tablets just to play this game forever. It is that good. And it's got so many songs by now, like easily over 300 on the EN version. The JP version must have broken the 400 milestone by now, and just about every single song is amazing. God Knows... on JP version is just... Chef's kiss Worth every penny spent on the VPN I needed to set up to make it work. (I know some people use the quooapp thingy, but I needed VPN for other stuff anyway so that was the way for me.)

My only gripe with the game : it uses a F2P mobile gatcha monetization scheme. I'm not a big fan of gatcha, I much prefer paying upfront for guaranteed content, but thankfully the rarer cards are in no way necessary to enjoy the game in full, unless you're gunning for those top positions on the event leaderboards, which is a full time job of it's own I never bothered with, but some do. Also big warning to anyone who can't resist the lure of waifu collecting. You will go broke. I managed to keep my spending... reasonable? Still dropped an average of 30 dollars on this game every month partially as a thank you to everyone involved for putting it out there. I'd have felt like a cheapskate otherwise. I despise all loot boxes mechanics on principle, yet I fed this monster around 450$. That is HOW GOOD this game is.

And now to see my favorite vtuber play my favorite rhythm game. 🤗 Thank you Gura, for being a fellow rhythm game lover. Much love from Canada. Once my Switch is returned to me (let the little brother burrow it) I'm gonna play other rhythm games you featured on this channel. Groove Coaster Wai Wai Party in particular because I love Touhou music so much and the Steam version of Groove Coaster is bad. So sad they blew it.
